\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0Hello, fellow zoos, and welcome to a very important new moon episode of Zooier Than Thou. I\'92m Fausty.\

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Toggle:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0And I\'92m Toggle, Doug Spink\'92s faithful lackey slash peon.\

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Fausty:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0And we\'92ll be your steadfast guides for this episode.\

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Toggle:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0We got a lot of positive comments on our last episode, but one of the funniest for us was, \'93Please stop doing comedy!\'94 Well, the good news is, we really don\'92t have a lot of funny things to say tonight. Suffice it to say, the past two weeks since the last episode have been intense.\

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Fausty:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0We\'92re going to attempt to lay everything out and make sense of it for you, tell you how we got to where we are now, and tell you what happens going forward. There\'92s a lot to unpack, and a lot of it\'92s unpleasant, but we feel like it\'92s very important to talk about.\

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Toggle:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0It started with the first e-mail we received, from someone called Shadowwoof who claimed to have insider knowledge of what happened with regards to Kero and the first leaks. He said, \'93I deal with this stuff. If you\'92re really in doubt, talk to me personally.\'94 And of course, he sent a link to a giant telegram archive which we specifically said we didn\'92t want. So I told him to contact Fausty, and he did.\

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Fausty:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0This guy came out of the door swinging. \'93I\'92ve been watching you for some time,\'94 just boasting and intimidating from the start. He said he had solid proof on Kero. Ok, so prove it. He couldn\'92t. Eventually, he conceded that there was no hard proof that Kero actually did anything, that everything was circumstantial. He then proceeded to tell me that he knew where I lived. Did you know I lived in Chicago, Toggle?\

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Toggle:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0Wow, that\'92s news to me! I could have sworn you explicitly said you lived in Harmony, Pennsylvania on one of our episodes for everyone to hear. Such savvy misdirection on your part!\

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Fausty:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0This is one of those conversations that\'92s really difficult to gloss or summarise. Early on, he threatens me with some sort of dire consequences \'96 not sure what I was or was not supposed to do to avoid this, but oh well. My immediate reaction, as is my usual policy, was to tell him to go ahead and do it \'96 whatever \'93it\'94 is. Best way to deal with threats is to jump right to the money shot and get it over with. Then you can loop back and continue doing what you were doing. Next I\'92m told I am dealing with the Leader of Online Zoos. Literally, that\'92s the title. This runs in circles, never leaving surreal along the way. I\'92m banned from a Telegram group I don\'92t belong to, accused of trying to out someone along the way (no idea who), reminded of dire consequences\'85 basically we\'92re going nowhere and I need a second set of eyes because I can\'92t make sense of any of this.\

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Toggle:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0At some point, Fausty pulled me into a group chat with this guy, and I\'92m already like, I want nothing to do with him. So we\'92re in this chat, with three different versions of Shadow, and he messages me on one of them like, \'93why are in you in this chat?\'94 And I\'92m like, \'93I was added to the chat.\'94 And he says, \'93Leave.\'94 So obviously, I didn\'92t leave, even though I wanted to. He called me a peon and a lackey, which was incredibly insulting, by the way, the whole time thrashing about and making demands. It became clear this guy was used to throwing his weight around and getting what he wanted out of people, and I wasn\'92t interested in being bullied around. So he kept harping about how we didn\'92t have any leverage on him, we couldn\'92t prove anything, you know, the types of things people don\'92t usually say when they\'92re innocent.\

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Fausty:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0That concept of \'93leverage\'94 and who does or does not have it has been put to me more in the past two weeks than in all the rest of my life. I\'92ve been told I don\'92t have leverage over people I don\'92t even know, apropos of nothing, more than once. Leverage? In this case, it\'92s someone who contacted us promising to correct errors in our last episode \'96 we got from there to leverage in no time whatsoever. And remember: this guy comes to us claiming to have info on Kero, and he doesn\'92t. Strike one. He threatens me, and tries to intimidate Toggle. Strike two. Then he claims credit for nailing the guy in Cuba, and that\'92s strike out, buddy. Also there\'92s more strikes \'96 correcting errors that he never even points out let alone corrects, threatening me with who-knows-what for no idea reason, creepy insinuations of being \'93local\'94 to me by repeatedly sending me pictures of hot dogs\'85 yes, hot dogs \'96 but really who\'92s counting by now? I\'92m ready to write off this guy as harmless but crazy, just a bunch of 2-legger politics and weird zoo power dynamics\'85 unfortunate, but unfortunately not uncommon. But then, something kind of clicked. Nobody legitimate uses zoosadism as background music for their Telegram shenanigans, do they? It\'92s at first just a hunch, a sense that there\'92s no possible way a discussion like this happens with someone living in what I now think of as the non-torture world. So I kept pressing him, by now so flagrantly that it risks tipping over into satire. This is completely not-fun, but I had a sense it might just pay off. It did.\

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Toggle:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0I was like, \'93I don\'92t know why you\'92re still goading him. But then fausty\'92s like, \'93This is why,\'94 and sends me a forwarded message Shadow sent from Akela accusing him of being a zoosadist. \'93After all,\'94 Akela writes, \'93the best way to hide as something is to pretend to be against the exact same thing.\'94\

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Fausty:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0Shadow sent me that to prove that he was friends with Akela? I have no real idea what he thought he was doing, but he went right into defensive mode after that. \'93Show me literally anything you have on me that links me stronger to zoosadism than Kero. Prove it. You can\'92t.\'94 That\'92s not how someone not tied up in this shit acts when confronted with such an accusation. This is something else we\'92ve seen way too much of the past two weeks: ask someone if they are a torturing sadist, and their reply is \'93you can\'92t prove that, there\'92s no proof.\'94 Well ok\'85 I mean an answer like that probably wouldn\'92t convince a 12-person jury beyond a reasonable doubt of guilt, buuuuut\'85 I can count how many times I\'92ve ever had that reply from anyone in my entire life, before this past 2 weeks, on one paw with toes to spare. Given that I\'92ve spent about six years of my life in various federal prisons, that\'92s kind of an interesting statistic.\

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Toggle:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0The conversation just got weirder and exponentially darker from there. Shadow started throwing everyone he could under the bus. He accused Akela of a profoundly destructive prediliction, after harping on what good friends they were. Brags that he\'92s untraceable, that he\'92s deleted all the evidence\'85 deleted all the evidence! \'96 even though of course fausty\'92s been screencapping everything in real time, says that he\'92ll just claim that the conversations are faked. Then the unthinkable happens.\

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Fausty:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0Well I\'92d been trying to make a Telegram voice connection for a while at the end of the chat \'96 mostly just to show that we\'92re still in reality-land here, and that we\'92re still just two male humans exchanging language. Bring things back to stable ground, as it were \'96 text chat can get pretty weird if left to its own devices. And he\'92s not answering, and I\'92m not surprised. But then, after I tell him I\'92ve heard all I need to know and I\'92ve got things to do, he calls me back. I take the call, tell him I\'92m recording it so I can share it with others if necessary, and confirm he\'92s ok with being recorded. He says yes. And I step through how I feel like our chat just went, what I feel like he\'92s tacitly admitted to being and doing, and how I feel it\'92s necessary to respond to such admissions. And by now he\'92s going backwards, denying having admitted anything, claiming to be the scourge of torturing sadists, and so on. I tell him he can\'92t even fucking figure out where I live from the hints such as me saying where I live in the last podcast episode he claims he\'92s calling in to correct errors in, so I\'92m not sure I can imagine him being the scourge of anything. Eventually I simply told him I\'92d heard what I needed, and that anyone else working with us could listen to the call, read the chat, and come to their own conclusions. My work, I told him, was done in this and he\'92d have to answer to folks with alot more power and authority than I in all this. By then, about six hours into this interaction, I admit that I\'92m fed up and angry. This is about god-damned torture of animals, and somehow this asshole has run in circles all the time without showing any signs he gives a shit about that. Like so much else we\'92ll soon experience, he seems much more focussed on the politics and appearance and power dynamics at play between different people and groups\'85 and the rounding error is torture. Well I\'92m sorry, but fuck that \'96 backwards priorities for me. Basically, I\'92ve concluded this guy is deep in the entire swirl of sadists and violent monsters we\'92re zeroing in on, and in his own words he\'92s functionally labelled himself as one already. So I\'92m done, call\'92s over. Oh and one more thing: in those hours of talking, he\'92s not once brought up nonhumans, concern for nonhumans, or frankly anything even vaguely zooish in any way. This was 100% 2-legger power politics\'85 from the ersatz Leader of Online Zoos. Fucking whatever, man.\

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Toggle:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0We felt the next best move was to talk to Akela, let him know what Shadow was saying, and find out his side of the story. We\'92re told that, immediately after fausty finished his call, Shadow went totally ape shit in the zooadmin telegram chat, threatening to go public with some logs that were under federal investigation in retaliation against Akela, whom he thought we\'92d already contacted but hadn\'92t. We\'92re getting pinged from every direction, asking us what the hell just happened, and we\'92re kind of not sure how to answer.\

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Fausty:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0Yep. From total strangers and old contact alike, I\'92m getting asked: \'93Man, what the fuck did you guys do? Shadow\'92s going apeshit!\'94 Since then, we\'92ve been slowly filling in the bigger picture piece by disgusting piece. It\'92s been a really unpleasant process.\

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Toggle:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0Oh, and keep in mind, in the background, Shadowwoof is spinning up fake accounts to message saying, \'93Hi, Fausty, Shadow\'92s not such a bad guy! Be nice to him!\'94 It\'92s like some bad parody of sockpuppeting, really only worth pity.\

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Fausty:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0There\'92s a lot of unpleasantness that followed in these conversations. Details of a consensual blackmail fetish group tied into these zoosadists, details of acts committed by different torturers, details of who was involved and how they were involved. Things were starting to make sense, how Akela was involved, how Kero was involved, how SnakeThing was involved\'85 and the fact that there were torturers that weren\'92t released in the first leaks in September, ringleaders that had been scrubbed from the leaks. Now, I have to pause and say that at this point, a lot of information we were receiving was misdirection. But in receiving it from multiple directions, we were able to begin piecing together what was real and what wasn\'92t. That\'92s a slow, frustrating process \'96 made necessary because so many of the people we\'92re now talking to are absolutely unapologetic and occasionally pathological liars. Someone tells you the sky is blue, you stick your head out the window to double-check. That bad. Over and over and over. Despite that, we can winnow down some baseline facts, some reliably-imputed structure, some well-defined areas where we\'92re still lacking reliable knowledge, and a whole bunch of mostly-reliable, internally-consistent, best-estimate-from-known-facts inferences and deductions. There\'92s a picture: some areas sharp, some blurry. But it\'92s a picture. An ugly fucking picture.\

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Toggle:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0Two things that were becoming consistent: one, Kero was being groomed by SnakeThing, likely since before he was a legal adult. Kero did participate in the sharing and consumption of torture videos, but he\'92d have moments of clarity where he\'92d be disgusted with himself and try to walk away, but he\'92d be back again the next day. Being groomed into this stuff is a soul-crushing process, and Kero was steeped in it for years. That he never ended up participating himself is noteworthy, given that information.\

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Fausty:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0As an aside, reading back through years of Kero\'92s logs and DMs, I can only say that we failed this young man as a community, first and foremost. He was so young when he showed up at BeastForum \'96 which, by the way, having 13 year olds in a porn forum maybe not such a fucking responsible decision, Beaker \'96 and nearly all the peer pressure he\'92s getting is to relax his ethics, not be so worried about a little violence, admit he likes the \'93hard stuff.\'94 What the fucking fuck. Seeing how that happened at BeastForum, I can only say that our worst suspicions of how noxious that forum had become don\'92t even come close to matching reality. Irrespective, the failure here is collective: this young man drifted deeper and deeper into a world of pure shit, and really nowhere along the way did anyone reach out and actually try to show a better path. Maybe everyone\'92s just too busy screaming about bullshit on twitter or whatever, but we all bear responsibility for an environment in which the most obvious place for a youngster to learn about our world is a noxious scamware site run by a drooling idiot hiding out in the UK. Back to number two: everyone we talked to was afraid of someone \'97 of Akela, of Shadowwoof, of each other, of \'93them,\'94 sometimes of Toggle and I. They all seemed to have leverage over each other. They all sought leverage over us, or claimed to have it already. Fucking leverage. Right now, I\'92d like to leverage this whole shitpile of broken souls into the ocean and pretend it never existed. Honestly. Fucking leverage.\

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Toggle:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0One thing to note is that when we approached this, we went very directly. It wasn\'92t about gaining leverage over people to blackmail them \'96 which, we realised, was a huge surprise to almost everyone in this. It was about saying, \'93Hey. Tell us what\'92s going on, or get the hell out of our way.\'94 And that seemed like a foreign language to these folks. No matter how much we\'92d simply say we\'92re looking to learn what happened and what\'92s happening now, most we talked to could not imagine any such thing. It was just a ruse, to try to get them to give us leverage. We\'92re trying to correct any errors in our little podcast, and like that we\'92re down a dark rabbit hole of blackmail, violence, lies, underage grooming, threats, and\'85 leverage, of course.\

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Fausty:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0So one particular person who\'92s been giving me a lot of information, he\'92s been acting a little suspicious. Just little things. I noticed at one point he stopped using periods when typing. \'93Oh, that\'92s weird,\'94 I said. \'93All your periods disappeared.\'94 \'93Stop being so paranoid!\'94 he said. Which was weird. I didn\'92t accuse him of anything. I just noticed his writing had changed a bit. Another, I answered his snarky question with \'93ok.\'94 Just \'93ok.\'94 He replies that I need to stop accusing everyone of being spies or sadists, if I want to have anyone talk to me. Huh? You got all that from \'93ok?\'94 These gruesome jumps were everywhere we turned, and you never know when you\'92ll ask a straightforward question and end up off in some parallel universe of lies and accusations as a direct result.\

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Toggle:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0Just to jump in: another unsettling theme was that it seemed every time we stumbled upon something legitimate, the person we were talking to would be like, \'93Stop being paranoid.\'94 Fausty is a paranoid motherfucker. Clinically paranoid. It\'92s fair to call him paranoid. But when every single time you say it, what he\'92s paranoid about ends up being true, it\'92s alarming confirmation of that paranoia. You can\'92t excuse a fact by insisting that fausty is paranoid and that\'92s why he uncovered the fact. That\'92s just not how reality works. He may be paranoid\'85 heck as he\'92ll tell you himself, he is paranoid \'96 and for good reason, if you ask me \'96 but that doesn\'92t change whether water is wet or gravity works even in a vacuum. They\'92re totally unrelated issues. I have seen fausty called paranoid right after he told someone he\'92s paranoid \'96 and more than once! Times like that, you really do have to laugh despite the ugliness of all this.\

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Fausty:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0Mostly I just tell people upfront: I\'92m normally suspicious and after what I\'92ve seen lately, I\'92m right up in full paranoid mode right now, so please don\'92t act surprised when I act suspicious. But it never works. We get into a talk, something doesn\'92t like up, I point that out, and \'93fuck you fausty, you paranoid fuck!\'94 Well sure ok\'85 but that still doesn\'92t line up. I dunno\'85 I wish I was imagining all this stuff, I really do. That\'92d be a much better world. With one guy, he\'92s lecturing me about how I don\'92t \'93get it\'94 and never will, and I\'92m asking him to explain \'93it,\'94 and he\'92s sort of dancing around and suggesting he can help\'85 but he doesn\'92t. And I\'92m sort of watching the clock, thinking \'93I could be doing literally anything but this right now\'85 why the hell and I talking to this tragically damaged human being I\'92ve never met and never will? And then he used the term \'93puppy splitter\'94 to describe one of the acts. Just out of the blue, like you might say \'93pipe cleaner\'94 or \'93estate planner.\'94 Puppy splitter. Horrific, just fucking horrific. And worse: it kind of sounded familiar. Where did I hear that before? So this guy seems particularly preoccupied with Rainstirs, asking for everything I know about him. That\'92s fine. I sent him an audio clip with details about it, only, out of paranoid habit, I changed a couple of details. Basically I said that I had helped hunt down Rainstirs and stop him (at least temporarily, unfortunately) from \'93cutting dogs open and fucking their entrails while they were still alive and screaming in pain.\'94 You know, the usual stuff \'96 just with \'93puppy\'94 changed to dog and one more change I prefer to keep private for future use. Stepping back, he started out by saying that he and Akela had been stalled for the past six months on their work, but later in the conversation, he said, \'93Well, you know, we\'92ve actually got this all under control, so don\'92t worry about it.\'94 Well, of course I\'92m worried about it. Animals are being tortured to death, and you\'92ve been sitting on your ass for six months, and now you\'92re trying to tell me it\'92s all under control? Bullshit. Also nobody has said a word about Rainstirs in all this yet. Nothing. I told the story only to demonstrate the absurdly awful things I\'92ve seen before, which yes Rainstirs, and suddenly someone\'92s echoing back details of Rainstirs\'92 evisceration techniques to me in perfect detail. Woah woah woah\'85 just fucking back this shit up a minute\'85\

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Toggle:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0Inserting another theme here. When we realized we were being misdirected, a common theme in that misdirection was, \'93Everything is under control. Just don\'92t do anything rash, or you could fuck everything up. We\'92ve got this.\'94\

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Fausty:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0Yes. Whenever things got awkward to the point of surreal, we\'92d fall into the \'93it\'92s all being handled, the details are secret, nothing to see here folks, move right along, these are not the torturers you are looking for\'94 black hole. So, in this convo, I tell him I have no intention of letting this go, and he starts demanding that I send him everything I have on Rainstirs. Rainstirs? Why Rainstirs. That was a decade ago. So I say, \'93OK, I\'92ll send you everything.\'94 And he\'92s like, \'93Good, good.\'94 \'93No, of course I\'92m not going to send you everything, you idiot.\'94 \'93Well, don\'92t you agree that he should be stopped?\'94 And then he proceeds to describe, in detail, the exact acts that Rainstirs committed, echoing back a puppy-based evisceration scenario\'85 and he also flips another little tidbit to the the way Rainstirs actually did things in his videos. So, right there, either you have watched all of Rainstirs videos amazingly closely (a disgusting job I\'92ve actually done but I hope few others have), or you are Rainstirs and you know how you did things in the videos. Neither of which lined up with who I was supposed to be talking to. Which, of course I\'92m paranoid, but I\'92m thinking the average person doesn\'92t just randomly switch \'93dog\'94 to \'93puppy\'94 in that wonderful little scene, when they repeat the unimaginably evil thing I\'92ve just told them in my voice message. Which\'85 I guess I\'92m paranoid for noticing that? When I pointed it out, he was like, \'93Oh, you know, I meant what you said before.\'94 \'93No, but you don\'92t understand. What you described by accident is exactly what Rainstirs did. Which means you\'92re either very familiar with Rainstirs\'92 videos, or you\'92re Rainstirs.\'94 And there was a pause. And he replied, \'93So what happens now?\'94 Well, I told him I had a PET scan that day, and it wasn\'92t good news. \'93How long you got,\'94 he asked. \'93Hard to say,\'94 I said. \'93I\'92m guessing maybe six months until I\'92m in the hospital. You think that\'92s enough time?\'94 \'93I don\'92t know,\'94 he said. \'93I do.\'94 He tells me that, oddly, he respects me \'96 I\'92m an ass, but he respects me. I tell him I can\'92t say the same about him, and he says he can certainly understand why. That happened, it really did. Now, this was in theory a chat with some furry kid who owns that account\'85 which yeah I guess maybe he just went haywire and said those things. I may be paranoid, but you\'92re gonna have to be one hell of a conspiracy theorist to explain how a random furry suddenly starts answering questions as Rainstirs. Because that\'92s what he was doing \'96 call it what you will, but that\'92s what it looks like.\

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Toggle:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0So Rainstirs, aka Tim Amaroso, reached out to us using a false account to find out what we knew about him. That\'92s what I\'92m seeing here. This was in a plaintext Telegram chat. Multiple folks can log into the same account in such chats and participate simultaneously in the same chat as the same account\'85\

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Fausty:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0Right, and later on when I pointed this out to Akela, he at first told me it couldn\'92t be done, then admitted maybe it could be done\'85 then told me that, go figure, he was logged into someone else\'92s Telegram account at the same time as them right then, as he was typing. So yes, I\'92m paranoid \'96 but you tell me if that\'92s the kind of thing you have happen on a daily basis. What are the chances, eh?\

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Toggle:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0Earlier in that conversation, someone said that he\'92d been a part of every zoosadism investigation squad from last September, which means he had access to all the information they had and was able to sabotage the work they were doing. Theoretically. If you\'92re paranoid.\

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Fausty:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0Furthermore, there were two people talking through that fake account \'96 I pointed this out, and was told that he was \'93sometimes walking outside and typed differently on his phone.\'94 Ok, maybe\'85 but then later it was \'93I have carpal tunnel,\'94 which makes no sense whatsoever as an explanation. Tim \'96 assuming one of the two was Tim, talking at the end \'96 didn\'92t use the same grammar as the first person. Does that \'93prove\'94 anything? Well, add in the otherwise-inexplicable inclusion of Tim-specific evisceration details, and the later admission that yes these folks do login concurrently to each others\'92 Telegram accounts\'85 and you tell me: what\'92s your conclusion, eh? Proof? No. But Occam says it walks and talks and quacks like a fucking puppy torturer, maybe don\'92t trust it around puppies.\

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Toggle:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0So at this point, we\'92re coming to these conclusions: First, the logs that Akela released in September were only meant to ruin SnakeThing \'97 and ruin is in quotes here. Some other people got leaked in the meantime, and they were super pissed and have been sweeping themselves under the rug since. Second, Kero was brought in and being groomed by Nel \'97 SnakeThing, that is. But they didn\'92t trust him; he wasn\'92t a monster, but he had a lot of potentially damaging information. So they took him down and marked him as a zoosadist and neutralized him as a threat. Which worked brilliantly by the way. Who would listen to Kero now if he pointed out nearly-unimaginable horrors or whatever else he knows but can\'92t really make stick after this horrible lynching he suffered.\

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Fausty:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0Third, these zoosadists joined all three investigation groups to misdirect and generate infighting within. All three groups melted down. Not entirely an accident. Fourth, the podcast picking this investigation back up and examining it was incredibly frustrating to the torturers left unpunished, who had apparently been breathing easy and felt their efforts had basically worked, which is why they started targeting us with misdirection and misinformation. Infiltrate, inject false \'93disclosures\'94 to us, create infighting, if possible. Misdirect our attention. We have seen exactly this pattern, in neon bright clarity. And the groups investigating this last year saw the exact same thing \'96 and fell apart thereafter.\

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Toggle:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0I\'92m sad to say that there was some infighting in our group. One thing that breaks down in this dark world is trust. Trust is so important for normal, healthy people, but it\'92s a liability when everyone you\'92re talking to is saying, \'93Trust me, it\'92s all OK,\'94 and lying through their teeth. Who can you trust? No one. Not even your friendly rat cohost, or other people involved I won\'92t name. No one can be trusted.\

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Fausty:
